main event: On March 7, 1956, in Lutz, Florida, there was a visual observation by a civilian of two objects moving ESE. The report concluded that there was insufficient data for analysis, suggesting a possible meteor sighting in the area at the same time.
interesting points: Insufficient data for analysis led to a possible meteor sighting conclusion.
The observation involved two round, red and white lights, which were described as 'two fat' and had no base or baseball shape.
The objects were observed to disappear after a short time, fading out slowly in about 1.5 seconds
There was no photograph included in the report.
The document contains references to multiple calls about similar objects and their positions over swamp and pasture land.
sighted object: two round, red and white lights
